=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>Zooming that far out provides a useful perspective. It&#8217;s a li=
ttle easier to accept that the things we hold true will change on that time=
scale. On a thousand year timescale, it&#8217;s much harder to imagine what=
 </span><em>won&#8217;t </em><span>change dramatically. And if history is a=
 guide, it&#8217;s hard to imagine that things won&#8217;t change for the b=
etter. The inconsequential things will fade away. The important things will=
 improve. New will replace old, as it always does.&#160;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: #404040; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><em>What</em><span> the better versions of everything will look like is a=
 complete unknown. But the process by which they&#8217;ll improve, at least=
